docs.abstract: As the Treasury Department prepared to enact the 2017 Republican tax overhaul, corporate lobbyists swarmed — and won big.

docs.lead_paragraph: The overhaul of the federal tax law in 2017 was the signature legislative achievement of Donald J. Trump’s presidency.

headline.main: How Big Companies Won New Tax Breaks From the Trump Administration
headline.print_headline: Business Got Big Tax Cut; Lobbyists Made It Bigger

byline.original: By Jesse Drucker and Jim Tankersley

docs.abstract: Every purchase evokes his design of the rectangular Universal Product Code. But although it became ubiquitous, he received no royalties.
docs.snippet: Every purchase evokes his design of the rectangular Universal Product Code. But although it became ubiquitous, he received no royalties.
docs.lead_paragraph: George J. Laurer, whose design of the vertically striped bar code sped supermarket checkout lines, parcel deliveries and assembly lines and even transformed human beings, including airline passengers and hospital patients, into traceable inventory items, died on Dec. 5 at his home in Wendell, N.C., near Raleigh. He was 94.

headline.main: George Laurer, Who Developed the Bar Code, Is Dead at 94
headline.print_headline: George Laurer, 94, Creator of Bar Code
